draw(A--M);
draw(B--D--C);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, NW);
label("$M$", M, S);
label("$\alpha$", (A + B)/2, SW);
label("$3\alpha$", (B + D)/2, NW);
[/asy]

Since $\angle BAC = \alpha,$ we have $\angle ABC = \angle ACB = \frac{180^\circ - \alpha}{2}.$  Since $\angle BDC = 3\alpha,$ we have $\angle BDA = \angle CDA = \frac{180^\circ - 3\alpha}{2}.$

