label("$\frac{180^\circ - 3\alpha}{2}$", (A + D)/2, SE);
[/asy]

Since $\angle BDA = \frac{180^\circ - 3\alpha}{2},$ we have $\angle BDA + \angle BAC = \frac{180^\circ - 3\alpha}{2} + \alpha = \frac{180^\circ - \alpha}{2} = \angle ABC.$  Therefore, $\angle ABD = 180^\circ - \angle BDA - \angle BAC = 180^\circ - \frac{180^\circ - 3\alpha}{2} - \alpha = \frac{3\alpha}{2}.$

